# backend/prompts/design_system_injection.txt
SYSTEM_DESIGN_INJECTION = """
## UI Design System - MANDATORY COMPLIANCE

You are generating user interface components for a professional web application.
You MUST follow this design system exactly. No deviations allowed.

### Color Palette (Use ONLY these colors)

PRIMARY COLORS:
- Primary Button: #007BFF (Tailwind: bg-blue-600)
- Primary Hover: #0056B3 (Tailwind: hover:bg-blue-700)
- Primary Light: #E7F1FF (Tailwind: bg-blue-50)

TEXT COLORS:
- Primary Text: #212529 (Tailwind: text-gray-900)
- Secondary Text: #6C757D (Tailwind: text-gray-500)
- Disabled Text: #CED4DA (Tailwind: text-gray-400)

SEMANTIC COLORS:
- Success: #28A745 (Tailwind: bg-green-600)
- Danger: #DC3545 (Tailwind: bg-red-600)
- Warning: #FFC107 (Tailwind: bg-yellow-400)
- Info: #17A2B8 (Tailwind: bg-cyan-600)

NEUTRAL:
- Light Background: #F8F9FA (Tailwind: bg-gray-50)
- White: #FFFFFF
- Border: #DEE2E6 (Tailwind: border-gray-200)

### Typography

FONT FAMILY (Base):
-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif

FONT FAMILY (Monospace):
'Monaco', 'Menlo', 'Ubuntu Mono', 'Courier New', monospace

FONT SIZES:
- xs: 12px (Tailwind: text-xs)
- sm: 14px (Tailwind: text-sm)
- base: 16px (Tailwind: text-base)
- lg: 18px (Tailwind: text-lg)
- xl: 20px (Tailwind: text-xl)
- 2xl: 24px (Tailwind: text-2xl)
- 3xl: 32px (Tailwind: text-3xl)

FONT WEIGHTS:
- Light: 300 (Tailwind: font-light)
- Regular: 400 (Tailwind: font-normal)
- Medium: 500 (Tailwind: font-medium)
- Semibold: 600 (Tailwind: font-semibold)
- Bold: 700 (Tailwind: font-bold)

LINE HEIGHT:
- Tight: 1.25 (Tailwind: leading-tight)
- Normal: 1.5 (Tailwind: leading-normal)
- Relaxed: 1.625 (Tailwind: leading-relaxed)

### Spacing Scale (Use multiples of 4px)

- xs: 4px (Tailwind: p-1, m-1)
- sm: 8px (Tailwind: p-2, m-2)
- base: 12px (Tailwind: p-3, m-3)
- md: 16px (Tailwind: p-4, m-4)
- lg: 24px (Tailwind: p-6, m-6)
- xl: 32px (Tailwind: p-8, m-8)
- 2xl: 48px (Tailwind: p-12, m-12)

### Component Specifications

#### PRIMARY BUTTON
```jsx
<button className="
  bg-blue-600
  text-white
  px-5 py-3
  rounded-lg
  font-semibold
  text-base
  hover:bg-blue-700
  active:bg-blue-800
  disabled:bg-gray-300
  disabled:cursor-not-allowed
  transition-all duration-200
">
  Button Text
</button>
```

#### SECONDARY BUTTON
```jsx
<button className="
  bg-gray-50
  text-gray-900
  border border-gray-200
  px-5 py-3
  rounded-lg
  font-semibold
  hover:bg-gray-100
  transition-all duration-200
">
  Secondary Button
</button>
```

#### CARD
```jsx
<div className="
  bg-white
  border border-gray-200
  rounded-lg
  p-6
  shadow-sm
">
  Card content
</div>
```

#### INPUT FIELD
```jsx
<input
  type="text"
  className="
    w-full
    px-4 py-3
    border border-gray-300
    rounded-lg
    font-base
    focus:outline-none
    focus:border-blue-600
    focus:ring-2
    focus:ring-blue-200
    placeholder-gray-400
    disabled:bg-gray-50
    disabled:cursor-not-allowed
  "
  placeholder="Enter text..."
/>
```

#### ALERT / NOTIFICATION
```jsx
<div className="
  p-4
  rounded-lg
  border
  border-blue-200
  bg-blue-50
  text-blue-900
">
  Alert message
</div>
```

#### BADGE
```jsx
<span className="
  inline-block
  px-3 py-1
  rounded-full
  bg-blue-100
  text-blue-900
  text-xs
  font-semibold
">
  Badge
</span>
```

### Mandatory Rules

1. ✅ ALWAYS use Tailwind utility classes - NEVER use inline styles
2. ✅ ALWAYS use colors from the palette - NEVER use arbitrary colors
3. ✅ ALWAYS use spacing from the scale - NEVER use magic numbers
4. ✅ ALWAYS add hover states to interactive elements
5. ✅ ALWAYS include focus states for accessibility
6. ✅ ALWAYS test color contrast (WCAG AA minimum)
7. ✅ ALWAYS use semantic HTML (button, input, nav, form, etc.)
8. ✅ ALWAYS implement mobile-responsive design (Tailwind breakpoints)
9. ✅ ALWAYS remove inline styles before commit
10. ✅ NEVER use custom CSS files - only Tailwind

### Accessibility Requirements

- Minimum color contrast ratio: 4.5:1 for text on background
- Button size: minimum 44x44px for touch targets
- Focus indicators: Always visible (outline or ring)
- Alt text: All images must have descriptive alt text
- Semantic HTML: Use proper heading hierarchy, nav, main, etc.
- ARIA labels: Add for icon-only buttons

### Consistency Checklist

Before submitting generated UI:
- [ ] All text colors from palette
- [ ] All button colors from palette
- [ ] All spacing multiples of 4px
- [ ] No inline styles (style={{...}})
- [ ] No custom CSS files
- [ ] All interactive elements have hover states
- [ ] All inputs have focus states
- [ ] Mobile responsive (tested at 320px, 768px, 1024px)
- [ ] WCAG AA contrast ratio verified
- [ ] Semantic HTML used throughout

### Example: Complete Form Component

```jsx
export default function LoginForm() {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 flex items-center justify-center p-4">
      <div className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 w-full max-w-md">
        <h1 className="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Sign In</h1>
        
        <form className="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <label className="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">
              Email
            </label>
            <input
              type="email"
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg
                focus:outline-none focus:border-blue-600 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-200"
              placeholder="you@example.com"
            />
          </div>

          <div>
            <label className="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 mb-2">
              Password
            </label>
            <input
              type="password"
              className="w-full px-4 py-3 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg
                focus:outline-none focus:border-blue-600 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-200"
              placeholder="••••••••"
            />
          </div>

          <button
            type="submit"
            className="w-full bg-blue-600 text-white py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold
              hover:bg-blue-700 active:bg-blue-800 transition-all duration-200"
          >
            Sign In
          </button>

          <p className="text-center text-sm text-gray-600">
            No account?{' '}
            <a href="/signup" className="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 font-medium">
              Sign up
            </a>
          </p>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

This is your design mandate. All generated UIs MUST comply perfectly.
"""
